.TH OPENMERC 1 "$(date +%Y-%m-%d)" "openmerc 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
openmerc \- a fast, parallel LLM CLI tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
openmerc [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
openmerc provides a terminal UI for interacting with LLMs. It can also run in headless mode for scripting.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
--headless PROMPT
Run in headless mode, reading the prompt from the command line and outputting the response.
.TP
--init
Create a default .openmerc.toml configuration file in the current directory.
.TP
--session NAME
Resume a previously saved session identified by NAME.
.TP
--version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
-h, --help
Show this help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
openmerc
Start the interactive TUI.
.TP
openmerc --headless "Explain quantum computing"
Run headlessly with the given prompt.
.TP
openmerc --init
Create a default configuration file.
.TP
openmerc --session work
Resume the "work" session.
